    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p>Never published before this edition.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><space quantity="2" unit="character"/> <orig>Σ</orig><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                    <lb n="2"/><space quantity="2" unit="character"/> <orig>Π</orig><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                    <lb n="3"/><w lemma="ἱαριτεύω">ἱα<supplied reason="lost"><certainty locus="name" match=".."/>ριτεύων</supplied></w> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
               </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>S<gap reason="lost"/> <supplied reason="subaudible">fils de</supplied>P<gap reason="lost"/> étant prêtre (?).</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>S<gap reason="lost"/> <supplied reason="subaudible">son of</supplied>P<gap reason="lost"/> being priest (?).</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>S<gap reason="lost"/> <supplied reason="subaudible">figlio di</supplied>P<gap reason="lost"/> quando era sacerdote (?).</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p/>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
             <p>With so poor vestiges, the reading is highly conjectural. The display might be the same as at <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr108700</ref>. The contrast in letter-height and axiality between lines 1-2 and line 3 
                 induces to restore the formula with 'being priest', rather than another personal name such as <foreign xml:lang="grc">Ἰἀσων</foreign>.</p>
            </div></body>
    </text>
